g5001.definition: [τάγμα] from {{g5021}}; something orderly in arrangement (a troop), i.e. (figuratively) a series or succession

g5002.definition: [τακτός] from {{g5021}}; arranged, i.e. appointed or stated

g5003.definition: [ταλαιπωρέω] from {{g5005}}; to be wretched, i.e. realize one's own misery

g5005.definition: [ταλαίπωρος] from the base of {{g5007}} and a derivative of the base of {{g3984}}; enduring trial, i.e. miserable

g5007.definition: [τάλαντον] neuter of a presumed derivative of the original form of τλάω (to bear; equivalent to {{g5342}}); a balance (as supporting weights), i.e. (by implication) a certain weight (and thence a coin or rather sum of money) or "talent"

g5008.definition: [ταλιθά] of Chaldee origin (compare {{h2924}}); the fresh, i.e. young girl; talitha (O maiden)

g5009.definition: [ταμεῖον] neuter contraction of a presumed derivative of ταμίας (a dispenser or distributor; akin to τέμνω, to cut); a dispensary or magazine, i.e. a chamber on the ground-floor or interior of an Oriental house (generally used for storage or privacy, a spot for retirement)

g5010.definition: [τάξις] from {{g5021}}; regular arrangement, i.e. (in time) fixed succession (of rank or character), official dignity

g5011.definition: [ταπεινός] of uncertain derivation; depressed, i.e. (figuratively) humiliated (in circumstances or disposition)

g5012.definition: [ταπεινοφροσύνη] from a compound of {{g5011}} and the base of {{g5424}}; humiliation of mind, i.e. modesty

g5013.definition: [ταπεινόω] from {{g5011}}; to depress; figuratively, to humiliate (in condition or heart)

g5015.definition: [ταράσσω] of uncertain affinity; to stir or agitate (roil water)

g5016.definition: [ταραχή] feminine from {{g5015}}; disturbance, i.e. (of water) roiling, or (of a mob) sedition

g5017.definition: [τάραχος] masculine from {{g5015}}; a disturbance, i.e. (popular) tumult

g5018.definition: [Ταρσεύς] from {{g5019}}; a Tarsean, i.e. native of Tarsus

g5019.definition: [Ταρσός] perhaps the same as ταρσός (a flat basket); Tarsus, a place in Asia Minor

g5020.definition: [ταρταρόω] from Τάρταρος (the deepest abyss of Hades); to incarcerate in eternal torment

g5021.definition: [τάσσω] a prolonged form of a primary verb (which latter appears only in certain tenses); to arrange in an orderly manner, i.e. assign or dispose (to a certain position or lot)

g5022.definition: [ταῦρος] apparently a primary word (compare {{h8450}}, "steer"); a bullock

g5023.definition: [ταῦτα] nominative or accusative case neuter plural of {{g3778}}; these things

g5024.definition: [ταὐτά] neuter plural of {{g3588}} and {{g846}} as adverb; in the same way

g5025.definition: [ταύταις] , and      ταύταςdative case and accusative case feminine plural respectively of {{g3778}}; (to or with or by, etc.) these

g5026.definition: [ταύτῃ] ,  and      ταύτην, and      ταύτηςdative case, accusative case and genitive case respectively of the feminine singular of {{g3778}}; (towards or of) this

g5028.definition: [τάφος] masculine from {{g2290}}; a grave (the place of interment)

g5029.definition: [τάχα] as if neuter plural of {{g5036}} (adverbially); shortly, i.e. (figuratively) possibly

g5030.definition: [ταχέως] adverb from {{g5036}}; briefly, i.e. (in time) speedily, or (in manner) rapidly

g5032.definition: [τάχιον] neuter singular of the comparative of {{g5036}} (as adverb); more swiftly, i.e. (in manner) more rapidly, or (in time) more speedily

g5033.definition: [τάχιστα] neuter plural of the superlative of {{g5036}} (as adverb); most quickly, i.e. (with {{g5613}} prefixed) as soon as possible

g5034.definition: [τάχος] from the same as {{g5036}}; a brief space (of time), i.e. (with {{g1722}} prefixed) in haste

g5035.definition: [ταχύ] neuter singular of {{g5036}} (as adverb); shortly, i.e. without delay, soon, or (by surprise) suddenly, or (by implication, of ease) readily

g5036.definition: [ταχύς] of uncertain affinity; fleet, i.e. (figuratively) prompt or ready

g5037.definition: [τέ] a primary particle (enclitic) of connection or addition; both or also (properly, as correlation of {{g2532}}) Often used in composition, usually as the latter participle.

g5038.definition: [τεῖχος] akin to the base of {{g5088}}; a wall (as formative of a house)

g5039.definition: [τεκμήριον] neuter of a presumed derivative of τεκμάρ (a goal or fixed limit); a token (as defining a fact), i.e. criterion of certainty

g5040.definition: [τεκνίον] diminutive of {{g5043}}; an infant, i.e. (plural figuratively) darlings (Christian converts)

g5041.definition: [τεκνογονέω] from a compound of {{g5043}} and the base of {{g1096}}; to be a child-bearer, i.e. parent (mother)

g5042.definition: [τεκνογονία] from the same as {{g5041}}; childbirth (parentage), i.e. (by implication) maternity (the performance of maternal duties)

g5043.definition: [τέκνον] from the base of {{g5088}}; a child (as produced)

g5044.definition: [τεκνοτροφέω] from a compound of {{g5043}} and {{g5142}}; to be a childrearer, i.e. fulfil the duties of a female parent

g5045.definition: [τέκτων] from the base of {{g5098}}; an artificer (as producer of fabrics), i.e. (specially), a craftsman in wood

g5046.definition: [τέλειος] from {{g5056}}; complete (in various applications of labor, growth, mental and moral character, etc.); neuter (as noun, with {{g3588}}) completeness

g5048.definition: [τελειόω] from {{g5046}}; to complete, i.e. (literally) accomplish, or (figuratively) consummate (in character)

g5049.definition: [τελείως] adverb from {{g5046}}; completely, i.e. (of hope) without wavering

g5050.definition: [τελείωσις] from {{g5448}}; (the act) completion, i.e. (of prophecy) verification, or (of expiation) absolution

g5052.definition: [τελεσφορέω] from a compound of {{g5056}} and {{g5342}}; to be a bearer to completion (maturity), i.e. to ripen fruit (figuratively)

g5053.definition: [τελευτάω] from a presumed derivative of {{g5055}}; to finish life (by implication, of {{g979}}), i.e. expire (demise)

g5055.definition: [τελέω] from {{g5056}}; to end, i.e. complete, execute, conclude, discharge (a debt)

g5056.definition: [τέλος] from a primary τέλλω (to set out for a definite point or goal); properly, the point aimed at as a limit, i.e. (by implication) the conclusion of an act or state (termination (literally, figuratively or indefinitely), result (immediate, ultimate or prophetic), purpose); specially, an impost or levy (as paid) Compare {{g5411}}.

g5057.definition: [τελώνης] from {{g5056}} and {{g5608}}; a tax-farmer, i.e. collector of public revenue

g5058.definition: [τελώνιον] neuter of a presumed derivative of {{g5057}}; a tax-gatherer's place of business

g5059.definition: [τέρας] of uncertain affinity; a prodigy or omen

g5060.definition: [Τέρτιος] of Latin origin; third; Tertius, a Christian

g5061.definition: [Τέρτυλλος] of uncertain derivation; Tertullus, a Roman

g5063.definition: [τεσσαρακονταετής] from {{g5062}} and {{g2094}}; of forty years of age

g5064.definition: [τέσσαρες] , or neuter      τέσσαραa plural number; four

g5066.definition: [τεταρταῖος] from {{g5064}}; pertaining to the fourth day

g5069.definition: [τετράδιον] neuter of a presumed derivative of τέτρας (a tetrad; from {{g5064}}); a quaternion or squad (picket) of four Roman soldiers

g5070.definition: [τετρακισχίλιοι] from the multiplicative adverb of {{g5064}} and {{g5507}}; four times a thousand

g5071.definition: [τετρακόσιοι] ,  or neuter      τετρακόσιαplural from {{g5064}} and {{g1540}}; four hundred

g5072.definition: [τετράμηνον] neuter of a compound of {{g5064}} and {{g3376}}; a four months' space

g5073.definition: [τετραπλόος] from {{g5064}} and a derivative of the base of {{g4118}}; quadruple

g5076.definition: [τετράρχης] from {{g5064}} and {{g757}}; the ruler of a fourth part of a country ("tetrarch")

g5077.definition: [τεφρόω] from τέφρα (ashes); to incinerate, i.e. consume

g5078.definition: [τέχνη] from the base of {{g5088}}; art (as productive), i.e. (specially), a trade, or (generally) skill

g5079.definition: [τεχνίτης] from {{g5078}}; an artisan; figuratively, a founder (Creator)

g5080.definition: [τήκω] apparently a primary verb; to liquefy

g5081.definition: [τηλαυγῶς] adverb from a compound of a derivative of {{g5056}} and {{g827}}; in a far-shining manner, i.e. plainly

g5082.definition: [τηλικοῦτος] , or feminine      τηλικαύτηfrom a compound of {{g3588}} with {{g2245}} and {{g3778}}; such as this, i.e. (in (figurative) magnitude) so vast

g5083.definition: [τηρέω] from τερός (a watch; perhaps akin to {{g2334}}); to guard (from loss or injury, properly, by keeping the eye upon; and thus differing from {{g5442}}, which is properly to prevent escaping; and from {{g2892}}, which implies a fortress or full military lines of apparatus), i.e. to note (a prophecy; figuratively, to fulfil a command); by implication, to detain (in custody; figuratively, to maintain); by extension, to withhold (for personal ends; figuratively, to keep unmarried); by extension, to withhold (for personal ends; figuratively, to keep unmarried)

g5084.definition: [τήρησις] from {{g5083}}; a watching, i.e. (figuratively) observance, or (concretely) a prison

g5085.definition: [Τιβεριάς] from {{g5086}}; Tiberias, the name of a town and a lake in Palestine

g5086.definition: [Τιβέριος] of Latin origin; probably pertaining to the river Tiberis or Tiber; Tiberius, a Roman emperor

g5087.definition: [τίθημι] ; a prolonged form of a primary      θέω       (which is used only as alternate in                               certain tenses); to place (in the widest application, literally and figuratively; properly, in a passive or horizontal posture, and thus different from {{g2476}}, which properly denotes an upright and active position, while {{g2749}} is properly reflexive and utterly  prostrate)

g5088.definition: [τίκτω] a strengthened form of a primary τέκω (which is used only as alternate in certain tenses); to produce (from seed, as a mother, a plant, the earth, etc.), literally or figuratively

g5089.definition: [τίλλω] perhaps akin to the alternate of {{g138}}, and thus to {{g4951}}; to pull off

g5090.definition: [Τιμαῖος] probably of Chaldee origin (compare {{h2931}}); Timæus (i.e. Timay), an Israelite

g5091.definition: [τιμάω] from {{g5093}}; to prize, i.e. fix a valuation upon; by implication, to revere

g5092.definition: [τιμή] from {{g5099}}; a value, i.e. money paid, or (concretely and collectively) valuables; by analogy, esteem (especially of the highest degree), or the dignity itself

g5093.definition: [τίμιος] ,        including the comparative      τιμιώτερος,  and the superlative      τιμιώτατοςfrom {{g5092}}; valuable, i.e. (objectively) costly, or (subjectively) honored, esteemed, or (figuratively) beloved

g5095.definition: [Τιμόθεος] from {{g5092}} and {{g2316}}; dear to God; Timotheus, a Christian

g5097.definition: [τιμωρέω] from a comparative of {{g5092}} and οὖρος ouros (a guard); properly, to protect one's honor, i.e. to avenge (inflict a penalty)

g5098.definition: [τιμωρία] from {{g5097}}; vindication, i.e. (by implication) a penalty

g5099.definition: [τίνω] ; strengthened for a primary      τίω    (which is only used as an alternate in                        certain tenses); to pay a price, i.e. as a penalty

g5100.definition: [τὶς] an enclitic indefinite pronoun; some or any person or object
